# Syncthing ignore rules.
# Applied locally by each device that has this folder configured. Committed to
# git so all machines share the same rules regardless of who syncs what.
#
# .git/ is excluded on purpose: git commit refs (HEAD, refs/heads/*, index) get
# rewritten frequently and Syncthing has no idea how to reconcile two devices
# that committed independently — it creates .sync-conflict files on refs, which
# git cannot recover from cleanly. Also, `git gc` can delete loose objects that
# a peer still references. Use the GitHub remote for history propagation.

/.git
